  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bc1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd ! \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b87\u0ba4\u0bcb !",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Register for National Fuel Permit! Here are the details!",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "Power Minister Kanchana Wijesekara has said that to get the QR code for the National Fuel Pass, they have to log into the website http://fuelpass.gov.lk and register their vehicles.",
        "He said the above while attending a press conference held at the Government Information Department and informing about the bond procedure for the national permit.",
        "Don't wait in queues at petrol stations owned by Sri Lankan Petroleum Corporations because the diesel fleet has arrived.",
        "Fuel will be dispensed at Sipetco filling stations only after the implementation of the \"National Fuel Permit System\".",
        "To get the QR code for the National Fuel Pass they need to log in to the website http://fuelpass.gov.lk and register their vehicles.",
        "Fuel will be distributed in limited quantities to any private vehicle that does not engage in public transport except buses and trains until the economic crisis in the country is resolved.",
        "Vehicles can be registered using National Identity Card, Passport Number, Trade or Business Registration Number. Only one QR code will be issued per vehicle.",
        "Until the implementation of the National Fuel Permit System, the Lanka I.O.C. He further informed that the fuel supply will continue as usual."
      ],
